qas.question: What was the name given to the island reached by Miguel Lopez de Legazpi on January 9th of 1530?
What is thought to be the modern name of the island Legazpi called Los Barbudos?
On what date did Legazpi's expedition see the island it named Placeres?
What name did the expedition give to the island it saw on January 12th?
What was the location of Corrales?
Who led the expedition involving the ship San Pedro?
What did Miguel López de Legazpi call the island discovered on January 9, 1530?
What did the Spanish call the island that might have been Ailuk?
On what day did the Spanish see the island they named Corrales?
What island may have been spotted by the Spanish on January 15?

context: The Spanish ship San Pedro and two other vessels in an expedition commanded by <a5_0>Miguel López de Legazpi<a5_0/> discovered an island on January 9, 1530, possibly <a1_0>Mejit<a1_0/>, at 10°N, which they named "<a0_0><a6_0>Los Barbudos<a6_0/><a0_0/>". The Spaniards went ashore and traded with the local inhabitants. On <a2_0>January 10<a2_0/>, the Spaniards sighted another island that they named "<a7_0>Placeres<a7_0/>", perhaps Ailuk; ten leagues away, they sighted another island that they called "Pajares" (perhaps Jemo). On <a8_0>January 12<a8_0/>, they sighted another island at <a4_0>10°N<a4_0/> that they called "<a3_0>Corrales<a3_0/>" (possibly Wotho). On January 15, the Spaniards sighted another low island, perhaps <a9_0>Ujelang<a9_0/>, at 10°N, where they described the people on "Barbudos". After that, ships including the San Jeronimo, Los Reyes and Todos los Santos also visited the islands in different years.
